Class SimulatedGpioProvider

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pi4j.io.gpio.GpioProviderBase
      • com.pi4j.io.gpio.SimulatedGpioProvider
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GpioProvider
    public class SimulatedGpioProvider
extends GpioProviderBase
implements GpioProvider
    A simulator to aid in development of RI Pi systems using a standard PC dev environment. To use the simulator you need two environment variables: The standard PI4J platform statement MUST point to the simulator: PI4J_PLATFORM=Simulated A second environment variable that defines the platform that is to be simulated. SimulatedPlatform={Real Platform's Name} e.g. SimultatedPlatform=RaspberryPi GPIO Provider If you don't provide a value for theSimulatedPlatform the system assumes that you want to use the raspberry pi platform: RaspiGpioProvider
    Author:
    bsutton
